{"body": "The `Object#===` operator is equal to the `Object#==` operator, but is usually overridden by several objects since it's used in `case` statements. When you call\r\n\r\n```ruby\r\ncase 'foobar'\r\nwhen /foo/\r\n  puts 'Foo'\r\nwhen /bar/\r\n  puts 'BAR!'\r\nend\r\n```\r\n\r\nRuby calls `'foobar' === /foo/` and `'foobar' === /bar/` (or vice-versa, I'm not quite sure). Thanks to the `===` operator being overridden, this actually works.", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/2665621", "created_at": "2011-11-08T09:58:01Z", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/1119#issuecomment-2665621", "updated_at": "2011-11-08T09:58:14Z", "repo": "rails", "issue_id": 1119, "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/henrikhodne/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/henrikhodne/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/henrikhodne/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/henrikhodne", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/henrikhodne/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/henrikhodne", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/henrikhodne/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://2.gravatar.com/avatar/d036be96167a38393d657c66a25ec85c?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2Ff1ab4591a72bfca2da721ca61a6e9569.png", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/henrikhodne/repos", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/henrikhodne/received_events", "gravatar_id": "d036be96167a38393d657c66a25ec85c", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/henrikhodne/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "login": "henrikhodne", "type": "User", "id": 24421, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/henrikhodne/followers"}, "owner": "rails", "_id": {"$oid": "52385d4dbd3543c151011fac"}, "id": 2665621, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/1119"}
